    Fake-chat memes are one of the most reliable formats on the internet. A single screenshot of a conversation — real or invented — can rack up millions of views because everyone texts, so everyone gets the joke instantly. The trick isn't the tool; it's the <strong>format</strong>. Below are 12 formats that reliably go viral, each with a copy-paste script template you can drop straight into a <a href="/editor">free chat generator</a> and export as a clean, watermark-free screenshot.
  </p>

  <p>
    Each template uses the same simple syntax: one message per line, <code>Name: message</code>. Paste it in, hit Generate, tweak the wording, and export. One quick rule before we start: keep these <strong>obviously fictional</strong> — memes and jokes are fine, passing fakes off as real receipts is not. More <a href="#ethics">at the end</a>.
  </p>

