  <h2>5. The group-chat chaos</h2>
  <p>Three or more people, one spiraling situation. Use group events for extra realism.</p>
  <pre><code>System: Aisha created group "Trip Planning ✈️"
Aisha: Ok so who's actually coming
Ben: Me!
Priya: In!
Ben: Wait where are we going
Priya: Nobody knows
Aisha: I already booked flights
Ben: TO WHERE</code></pre>

  <h2>6. The corporate-speak translation</h2>
  <p>What they said vs. what they meant. Perfect on Slack styling for office humor.</p>
  <pre><code>Boss: Hey, quick question when you get a sec!
Me: sure what's up
Boss: Can you "circle back" on that thing "at some point"
Me: which thing
Boss: You'll know 🙂
Me: I will not know</code></pre>

  <h2>7. The AI-got-too-real</h2>
  <p>You ask an AI something innocent; the answer hits different. Underused and does numbers.</p>
  <pre><code>Me: Write me a motivational quote
ChatGPT: "You're not behind. You just measured yourself against a version of you that doesn't exist."
Me: I asked for a QUOTE not an attack
ChatGPT: Would you like a gentler one?
Me: no it's too late now</code></pre>

  <h2>8. The parent discovering technology</h2>
  <p>The formatting itself is the joke — random capitals, full names, sign-offs.</p>
  <pre><code>Dad: Hello Son. This Is Your Father.
Me: dad i know it's you
Dad: How Do I Attach The Photo Of The Dog
Me: just tap the camera icon
Dad: Which One Is The Dog
Dad: - Dad</code></pre>

  <h2>9. The overly dramatic order confirmation</h2>
  <p>Turn a mundane exchange into high stakes. Works because the format is so familiar.</p>
  <pre><code>Me: hey are you coming to the thing
Sam: what thing
Me: THE thing
Sam: I have no memory of a thing
Me: it's your birthday party
Sam: cancel it</code></pre>

  <h2>10. The relationship timeline</h2>
  <p>Same two people, "then vs. now." One screenshot, the whole arc.</p>
  <pre><code>Date: Year 1
Me: good morning beautiful ❤️ can't wait to see you
Date: Year 5
Me: did you eat the last yogurt
You: maybe
Me: this relationship is over</code></pre>

  <h2>11. The customer-service standoff</h2>
  <p>Person vs. bot, escalating politely into madness.</p>
  <pre><code>Me: I'd like to cancel my subscription
Support: We're so sad to see you go! Can we offer 10% off?
Me: No thanks, just cancel
Support: How about 20% off? 💙
Me: Cancel. Please.
Support: Have you considered staying forever?</code></pre>

  <h2>12. The unhinged best friend</h2>
  <p>Zero judgment, terrible advice, instant support. Relatable to anyone with a group chat.</p>
  <pre><code>Me: I think I made a huge mistake
Kayla: did you commit a crime
Me: no
Kayla: then we can fix it
Me: I texted my ex
Kayla: ok THAT'S a crime</code></pre>

